results.name: Primes p such that q-p = 180, where q is the next prime after p.
link: Luke March, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000 (First 100 terms from _M. F. Hasler_)
Index entries for primes, gaps between
mathematica: a = {}; Do[If[Prime[x + 1] - Prime[x] == 180, AppendTo[a, Prime[x]]], {x, 1, 100000}]; a
program: (PARI) p=0; g=180; for(c=1,100, while(g+p!=p=nextprime(p+1),); write("c:/temp/gap-"g".txt", c" "p-g))
